IRS990.MissionDesc: PROVIDE SUPPORT FOR THE UCLA HEALTH SYSTEM PROGRAMS AND PATIENTS.
IRS990.Desc: THE ORGANIZATION OPERATES A THRIFT STORE AND THREE GIFT SHOPS TO BENEFIT THE PATIENTS, FAMILIES, EMPLOYEES AND GENERAL PUBLIC AT THE RONALD REAGAN UCLA MEDICAL CENTER; THE UCLA MEDICAL CENTER, SANTA MONICA, CA; MATTEL CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL UCLA AND THE RESNICK NEUROPSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL AT UCLA.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part IV, Section D, Line 2: Organizaiton Maintained A Relationship with Supported Orgs.
Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS MAINTAINS CLOSE TIES WITH THE UCLA HEALTH SYSTEM, TAKING THEIR REQUESTS AND PROVIDING LIASIONS ON A REGULAR BASIS.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part IV, Section E, Line 2a: Identify Supported Orgs. and Explain How Activities Furthered Exempt Pu
Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION OPERATES GIFT SHOPS IN THE UCLA HEALTH SYSTEM BUILDINGS PLUS A THRIFT SHOP OWNED BY THE AUXILIARY, PROVIDING PATIENTS AND VISITORS AN IMPORTANT PLACT TO VISIT BEFORE, DURING AND AFTER MEDICAL PROCEDURES, SURGERY AND ROUTINE VISITS.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part IV, Section E, Line 2b: Reasons For The Organization's Position
Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: HAD THE ORGANIZATION NOT BEEN PERFORMING THESE SERVICES, UCLA HEALTH SYSTEM WOULD HAVE HAD TO RUN THESE OPERATIONS ON THEIR OWN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Management has evaluated its tax positions and has concluded that a provision for a tax liability is not necessary at June 30, 2018.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GRANTS ARE AWARDED TO THE UCLA MEDICAL CENTER FOR EDUCATION SERVICES, PATIENT AID AND EQUIPMENT. ALL GRANTS ARE APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BASED ON REQUESTS FROM THE MEDICAL CENTER FOR SPECIFIC ITEMS OR SERVICES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS CAREFULLY REVIEWED BY THE CO-TREASURERS, PRESIDENT AND A VOLUNTEER CONSULTING CPA PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH BOARD MEMBER SIGNS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLOICY AT THE START OF THE FISCAL YEAR AFFIRIMING THAT THEY UNDERSTAND AND WILL ABIDE BY THE POLICY. ANY MEMBER WITH A POTENTIAL CONFLICT IS EXPECTED TO REFRAIM FROM DISCUSSION AND VOTING ON THE ISSUE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNUAL SALARY AND PERFORMANCE RECIEWS ARE DONE BY THE HUMAN RESOURCES COMMITTEE, THE BOARD PRESIDENT, VICE PRESIDENT AND THE DIRECTOR OF RETAIL OPERATIONS. SALARIES ARE BASED ON PERFORMANCE AND THE FINANCIAL CONDITION OF THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ORGANIZING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
